{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849305275,"sessionID":"ses_28722acb8ffeSzUCOs5XZII0o3","part":{"id":"prt_d78ddee91001eXA9n0VkUFQCNM","messageID":"msg_d78ddd2b600119Hbh6xL5JDHaf","sessionID":"ses_28722acb8ffeSzUCOs5XZII0o3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7db61aab3b0944d990c6fa52","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009: Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal defines the HTTP reverse proxy core implementation for the `pkg/router` module in the AgentCube project. The router is responsible for:\n6: \n7: 1. **Session-aware traffic routing** - Resolve or create sessions via workload manager, route HTTP requests to appropriate sandbox endpoints\n8: 2. **Reverse proxy functionality** - Proxy HTTP traffic to sandbox pods with proper URL rewriting and header forwarding\n9: 3. **JWT authentication** - Sign outbound requests to sandboxes with JWT tokens for authentication\n10: 4. **Connection management** - Handle connection pooling, health checks, and concurrency limiting\n11: 5. **Activity tracking** - Update session last-activity timestamps in the store for idle cleanup\n12: \n13: The router serves as the primary entry point for all HTTP invocations targeting agent runtimes and code interpreters.\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n18: **Language:** Go  \n19: **Size:** M\n20: \n21: ### In Scope\n22: \n23: 1. **Session Manager** (`pkg/router/session/manager.go`)\n24:    - `SessionManager` interface and implementation\n25:    - Session resolution from `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n26:    - Workload manager integration for session creation\n27:    - `SandboxInfo` caching and lookup\n28: \n29: 2. **Reverse Proxy Core** (`pkg/router/proxy/proxy.go`)\n30:    - `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy` wrapper\n31:    - Custom `Director` for URL rewriting and header injection\n32:    - JWT generation and injection for sandbox authentication\n33:    - Error handling and response mapping\n34: \n35: 3. **Routing Rules Engine** (`pkg/router/routing/rules.go`)\n36:    - Entry point selection by path matching\n37:    - Protocol normalization (http/https)\n38:    - URL scheme detection and prefixing\n39: \n40: 4. **Connection Pooling** (`pkg/router/pool/pool.go`)\n41:    - Shared `http.Transport` configuration\n42:    - Connection reuse settings\n43:    - Idle connection management\n44: \n45: 5. **Health Check System** (`pkg/router/health/checker.go`)\n46:    - Liveness endpoint (`/health/live`)\n47:    - Readiness endpoint (`/health/ready`)\n48:    - Dependency health verification\n49: \n50: 6. **HTTP Server** (`pkg/router/server.go`)\n51:    - Gin router setup with middleware stack\n52:    - HTTP/2 and h2c support\n53:    - TLS configuration\n54:    - Graceful shutdown\n55: \n56: 7. **Middleware Components**\n57:    - Concurrency limiting semaphore (`pkg/router/middleware/semaphore.go`)\n58:    - Gin logger and recovery\n59:    - Forwarding headers injection (`X-Forwarded-Host`, `X-Forwarded-Proto`, `X-Forwarded-For`)\n60: \n61: 8. **JWT Manager** (`pkg/router/auth/jwt.go`)\n62:    - RS256 JWT signing\n63:    - Key generation and storage (`picod-router-identity` secret)\n64:    - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` bootstrap logic\n65: \n66: 9. **Invocation Handlers** (`pkg/router/handler/invocation.go`)\n67:    - AgentRuntime invocation endpoint\n68:    - CodeInterpreter invocation endpoint\n69:    - Session resolution and activity tracking\n70: \n71: ### Out of Scope\n72: \n73: - Workload Manager reconciler logic (separate controller component)\n74: - Session store implementation (uses existing `pkg/store` module)\n75: - CRD type definitions (defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`)\n76: - Python SDK CLI commands (separate Python package)\n77: - PicoD daemon inside sandboxes (separate `picod` binary)\n78: - Agentd idle cleanup controller (separate controller component)\n79: - Volcano scheduler integration (optional, separate component)\n80: \n81: ## Impact Analysis\n82: \n83: ### Dependencies\n84: \n85: | Dependency | Type | Reason |\n86: |------------|------|--------|\n87: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Required | Generated Kubernetes client for Secret operations |\n88: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Required | In-cluster config, Secret API |\n89: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Required | Secret, ServiceAccount types |\n90: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | Required | Kubernetes error handling |\n91: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | Required | HTTP framework |\n92: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | Required | JWT signing (RS256) |\n93: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Required | Session store client |\n94: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Required | Session store interface |\n95: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Required | Type constants (kinds) |\n96: | `net/http/httputil` | Required | Reverse proxy |\n97: | `golang.org/x/net/http2` | Required | HTTP/2 support |\n98: \n99: ### Downstream Consumers\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 569. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009: Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal defines the HTTP reverse proxy core implementation for the `pkg/router` module in the AgentCube project. The router is responsible for:\n\n1. **Session-aware traffic routing** - Resolve or create sessions via workload manager, route HTTP requests to appropriate sandbox endpoints\n2. **Reverse proxy functionality** - Proxy HTTP traffic to sandbox pods with proper URL rewriting and header forwarding\n3. **JWT authentication** - Sign outbound requests to sandboxes with JWT tokens for authentication\n4. **Connection management** - Handle connection pooling, health checks, and concurrency limiting\n5. **Activity tracking** - Update session last-activity timestamps in the store for idle cleanup\n\nThe router serves as the primary entry point for all HTTP invocations targeting agent runtimes and code interpreters.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775849305260,"end":1775849305274}}}}
