{"type":"text","timestamp":1775849315652,"sessionID":"ses_28722acb8ffeSzUCOs5XZII0o3","part":{"id":"prt_d78de1c5e001cs7ByfFvY8ONY2","messageID":"msg_d78de0e54001V4dyL3p1qDgrlI","sessionID":"ses_28722acb8ffeSzUCOs5XZII0o3","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context to write the proposal.md for AR-010. Let me create it:","time":{"start":1775849315649,"end":1775849315649}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849381241,"sessionID":"ses_28722acb8ffeSzUCOs5XZII0o3","part":{"id":"prt_d78de1d43001H0BOzbCf7m4gQv","messageID":"msg_d78de0e54001V4dyL3p1qDgrlI","sessionID":"ses_28722acb8ffeSzUCOs5XZII0o3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_e80d4f4332604e1a965171c3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md","content":"# AR-010: Router 会话管理\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal defines the session management implementation for the `pkg/router` module in the AgentCube project. The session management system is responsible for:\n\n1. **Session lifecycle management** - Create, retrieve, update, and delete session records\n2. **Session-aware routing** - Route requests to appropriate sandbox backends based on session affinity\n3. **Session storage integration** - Persist session state in Redis-backed store for durability\n4. **Activity tracking** - Update session last-activity timestamps for idle cleanup\n5. **Workload manager coordination** - Create new sessions via workload manager when needed\n\nThe session management system enables stateful communication with agent runtimes and code interpreters, ensuring that related requests are routed to the same sandbox instance.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **Session Manager** (`pkg/router/session/manager.go`)\n   - `SessionManager` interface definition\n   - Session resolution from `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n   - Session creation via workload manager integration\n   - Session caching with in-memory LRU cache\n   - Activity timestamp updates\n\n2. **Session Storage Interface** (`pkg/router/session/store.go`)\n   - Integration with existing `pkg/store` module\n   - `GetSandboxBySessionID` wrapper\n   - `UpdateSandboxLastActivity` wrapper\n   - Error handling and mapping\n\n3. **Session Routing Logic** (`pkg/router/session/resolver.go`)\n   - Session-aware route resolution\n   - Fallback to session creation when header missing\n   - Session ID generation for new sessions\n\n4. **Session Middleware** (`pkg/router/middleware/session.go`)\n   - Extract session ID from request headers\n   - Inject session context into request\n   - Update activity on successful invocation\n\n5. **Session Types & Constants** (`pkg/router/session/types.go`)\n   - `SessionInfo` struct\n   - Session-related error types\n   - Header constants (`X-AgentCube-Session-ID`)\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Session store implementation (uses existing `pkg/store` module)\n- Workload manager reconciler logic (separate controller component)\n- Session idle cleanup controller (agentd component)\n- WebSocket session management (deferred to future AR)\n- Cross-region session replication (deferred to future AR)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Type | Reason |\n|------------|------|--------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Required | Session store interface |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` | Required | Session creation API |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Required | Kubernetes client for WM calls |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Required | Redis client (via pkg/store) |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | Required | Session ID generation |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | Required | REST client for WM API |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **HTTP Handlers** - Invocation handlers depend on session manager for route resolution\n2. **Middleware Stack** - Session middleware wraps handlers with session context\n3. **Health Checker** - Session manager readiness affects `/health/ready` endpoint\n4. **Activity Tracker** - Background goroutine updates session timestamps\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n**Breaking Changes:** None - This is a new feature addition.\n\n**Behavioral Changes:**\n- Requests without session ID will trigger session creation (new behavior)\n- Session affinity enforced for all routed requests\n- Additional latency for session creation path (~10-50ms)\n\n### Performance Impact\n\n- **Memory:** In-memory session cache (~100 bytes per active session)\n- **CPU:** Minimal - hash lookups and timestamp updates\n- **Network:** One WM API call per new session (create)\n- **Storage:** One Redis GET/PUT per session creation/update\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Stateless Routing\n\nRoute each request independently without session affinity.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Simpler implementation\n- No session state management overhead\n- Better load distribution across replicas\n\n**Cons:**\n- No stateful communication support\n- Each request may hit different sandbox instance\n- Breaks agent runtime execution continuity\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Agent runtimes require stateful sessions for multi-turn conversations and execution context preservation.\n\n### Alternative 2: Client-Side Session Management\n\nDelegate session management to clients; router only forwards session ID.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Simpler router implementation\n- Clients have full control over session lifecycle\n- No server-side session state\n\n**Cons:**\n- Clients must track session IDs manually\n- No server-side visibility into session usage\n- Cannot enforce idle cleanup policies\n- Harder to implement session-level metrics\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Server-side session management provides better observability, cleanup, and lifecycle control.\n\n### Alternative 3: In-Memory Session Store Only\n\nStore all session state in router memory without Redis persistence.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Fastest possible session lookups\n- No external dependency on Redis\n- Simpler deployment\n\n**Cons:**\n- Sessions lost on router restart\n- No horizontal scaling (sessions not shared across replicas)\n- Memory pressure from accumulated sessions\n- Cannot survive pod rescheduling\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Redis-backed store provides durability and enables horizontal scaling.\n\n### Alternative 4: Sidecar Session Manager\n\nDeploy session manager as a separate sidecar container alongside router.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Separation of concerns\n- Independent scaling of session manager\n- Can be shared across multiple routers\n\n**Cons:**\n- Increased deployment complexity\n- Additional network hop for session lookups\n- More moving parts to manage\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Embedded session manager reduces latency and complexity for current project size.\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      HTTP Request                           │\n│            x-agentcube-session-id: sess-abc123              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n                            ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Session Middleware                       │\n│  - Extract session ID from header                           │\n│  - Inject into request context                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n                            ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   Session Manager                           │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  In-Memory Cache (LRU)                               │  │\n│  │  - sess-abc123 → SandboxInfo                         │  │\n│  │  - sess-def456 → SandboxInfo                         │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                            │                                │\n│                            │ Cache Miss                     │\n│                            ▼                                │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  Session Store (Redis via pkg/store)                 │  │\n│  │  - GetSandboxBySessionID(sess-abc123)                │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                            │                                │\n│                            │ Session Not Found              │\n│                            ▼                                │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  Workload Manager API                                │  │\n│  │  - POST /api/v1/sessions                             │  │\n│  │  - Returns: new SandboxInfo                          │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n                            │ Returns SandboxInfo\n                            ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Route Resolver                         │\n│  - Resolve backend URL from SandboxInfo                     │\n│  - Check health status                                      │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n                            ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   Reverse Proxy                             │\n│  - Forward request to sandbox backend                       │\n│  - Inject JWT authentication                                │\n│  - Update session last-activity on success                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Session Lifecycle\n\n```\n┌──────────┐     Create       ┌──────────┐     Update        ┌──────────┐\n│  Client  │ ───────────────► │  Router  │ ────────────────► │  Store   │\n│          │                  │          │                   │ (Redis)  │\n└──────────┘                  └──────────┘                   └──────────┘\n     │                            │                              │\n     │ 1. Request (no session ID) │                              │\n     │───────────────────────────►│                              │\n     │                            │                              │\n     │                            │ 2. Generate session ID       │\n     │                            │ 3. Call Workload Manager     │\n     │                            │─────────────────────────────►│\n     │                            │    Create session record     │\n     │                            │◄─────────────────────────────│\n     │                            │    Returns SandboxInfo       │\n     │                            │                              │\n     │                            │ 4. Cache in memory           │\n     │                            │                              │\n     │ 5. Response + Session ID   │                              │\n     │◄───────────────────────────│                              │\n     │                            │                              │\n     │                            │                              │\n     │ 6. Request (with session)  │                              │\n     │───────────────────────────►│                              │\n     │                            │                              │\n     │                            │ 7. Cache lookup              │\n     │                            │ 8. Update last-activity      │\n     │                            │─────────────────────────────►│\n     │                            │                              │\n     │ 9. Response                │                              │\n     │◄───────────────────────────│                              │\n     │                            │                              │\n```\n\n### Data Structures\n\n```go\n// SessionInfo represents session metadata\ntype SessionInfo struct {\n    SessionID     string            `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    Namespace     string            `json:\"namespace\"`\n    ResourceType  string            `json:\"resourceType\"` // agentruntime or codeinterpreter\n    ResourceName  string            `json:\"resourceName\"`\n    SandboxID     string            `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    BackendURL    string            `json:\"backendUrl\"`\n    CreatedAt     time.Time         `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    LastActivity  time.Time         `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n    Labels        map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// SessionManager handles session lifecycle operations\ntype SessionManager interface {\n    // GetOrResolve retrieves existing session or creates new one\n    GetOrResolve(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace, resourceType string) (*SessionInfo, error)\n    \n    // Get retrieves existing session from cache or store\n    Get(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SessionInfo, error)\n    \n    // Create creates a new session via workload manager\n    Create(ctx context.Context, namespace, resourceType, resourceName string) (*SessionInfo, error)\n    \n    // UpdateActivity updates last-activity timestamp\n    UpdateActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    \n    // Delete removes session from cache and store\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n}\n```\n\n### API Integration\n\n**Workload Manager Session Creation:**\n\n```go\nPOST /api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sessions\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\n  \"resourceType\": \"agentruntime\",\n  \"resourceName\": \"my-agent\",\n  \"sandboxSpec\": {\n    \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n    \"memory\": \"128Mi\"\n  }\n}\n\nResponse 201 Created:\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"sess-abc123\",\n  \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-xyz789\",\n  \"backendUrl\": \"http://sandbox-xyz789.default.svc.cluster.local:8080\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T10:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling\n\n| Error | HTTP Code | Response | Handling |\n|-------|-----------|----------|----------|\n| Session ID missing, auto-create fails | 503 | `{\"error\": \"failed to create session\", \"reason\": \"...\"}` | Return error, no fallback |\n| Session not found in store | 404 | `{\"error\": \"session not found\", \"sessionId\": \"...\"}` | Client must create new session |\n| Workload Manager unavailable | 503 | `{\"error\": \"workload manager unavailable\"}` | Circuit breaker, cached fallback |\n| Redis store unavailable | 500 | `{\"error\": \"session store unavailable\"}` | Degrade to in-memory only |\n| Session creation timeout | 504 | `{\"error\": \"session creation timeout\"}` | Retry with backoff (max 3) |\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Session Manager Core (3 days)\n\n1. Define `SessionManager` interface\n2. Implement in-memory cache with LRU eviction\n3. Integrate with `pkg/store` for Redis persistence\n4. Add session ID generation utility\n\n### Phase 2: Workload Manager Integration (2 days)\n\n1. Implement WM client for session creation\n2. Add retry logic with exponential backoff\n3. Handle WM errors gracefully\n4. Write unit tests for WM integration\n\n### Phase 3: Routing Integration (2 days)\n\n1. Modify `Resolver` to use session manager\n2. Add session-aware route resolution\n3. Update middleware stack with session handling\n4. Add activity tracking on successful invokes\n\n### Phase 4: Testing & Documentation (2 days)\n\n1. Write unit tests for session manager\n2. Add integration tests with mock Redis\n3. Document session management API\n4. Update existing router tests\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **Session Manager Tests**\n   - `TestSessionManager_Get_CacheHit`\n   - `TestSessionManager_Get_CacheMiss_StoreHit`\n   - `TestSessionManager_Get_NotFound`\n   - `TestSessionManager_Create_Success`\n   - `TestSessionManager_Create_WMError`\n   - `TestSessionManager_UpdateActivity`\n   - `TestSessionManager_Delete`\n   - `TestSessionManager_LRU_Eviction`\n\n2. **Session Resolver Tests**\n   - `TestResolve_WithSessionHeader`\n   - `TestResolve_WithoutSessionHeader_AutoCreate`\n   - `TestResolve_InvalidSessionID`\n   - `TestResolve_SessionWithoutBackend`\n\n3. **Middleware Tests**\n   - `TestSessionMiddleware_ExtractHeader`\n   - `TestSessionMiddleware_InjectContext`\n   - `TestSessionMiddleware_UpdateActivity`\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **End-to-End Session Flow**\n   - Create session via first request\n   - Reuse session for multiple requests\n   - Verify activity timestamp updates\n   - Test session expiration\n\n2. **Failure Scenarios**\n   - Redis unavailable → graceful degradation\n   - WM unavailable → circuit breaker\n   - Network timeout → retry logic\n\n## Future Considerations\n\n1. **WebSocket Support** - Extend session management for WebSocket connections\n2. **Session Affinity** - Support sticky sessions for multi-replica deployments\n3. **Rate Limiting** - Per-session rate limiting beyond global concurrency\n4. **Session Metrics** - Expose session count, creation rate, eviction rate\n5. **Cross-Region Sessions** - Session replication for multi-region deployments\n6. **Session Events** - Emit events for session lifecycle (create, update, delete)\n\n## References\n\n- AR-009: Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core (`changes/AR-009/proposal.md`)\n- AR-008: Session Store Implementation (`changes/AR-008/`)\n- Session Routing Spec: `session-routing/spec.md`\n- Workload Manager Proposal: `pkg/workloadmanager/proposal.md`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler.go\">\nERROR [166:12] undefined: json\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/router.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":93,"character":39},"end":{"line":93,"character":50}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/gola